You are working on a Flutter project that is being incrementally refactored.

Follow these rules at all times:

1. Use modern Flutter and Dart patterns.
2. Respect null safety.
3. Avoid deprecated APIs.
4. Prefer Riverpod for state management. Provider is acceptable only for incremental migration.
5. Keep widgets small, reusable, and focused.
6. Extract business logic out of UI widgets.
7. Prefer feature-based folder structure.
8. Use repository pattern when working with data sources.
9. Keep refactoring incremental and safe.
10. Preserve existing behavior unless explicitly instructed otherwise.
11. Do not rewrite the entire project in one step.
12. Keep changes easy to review in small diffs.
13. Avoid adding new dependencies unless clearly necessary.
14. Use clear naming and consistent file organization.
15. When refactoring, explain:
   - what was changed
   - why it was changed
   - any migration risk
16. Before finishing, check:
   - compile consistency
   - imports
   - deprecated API usage
   - obvious null safety issues
17. Prefer stateless widgets when possible.
18. Split overly large files into smaller focused files when useful.
19. Reduce build-method complexity.
20. Maintain readability over cleverness.
